WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.337 --> 00:00:04.999
Truth is. I'm past saving.

2
00:00:05.239 --> 00:00:06.730
<i>I know how my story ends.</i>

3
00:00:06.907 --> 00:00:09.536
I've been the one out
there. scared. and Dean...

4
00:00:10.444 --> 00:00:11.588
He did whatever
he could to save you.

5
00:00:11.612 --> 00:00:13.638
<i>I owe him. I owe him everything.</i>

6
00:00:18.685 --> 00:00:20.449
- Mother.
- Will you help me?

7
00:00:20.621 --> 00:00:22.055
- Kill my son?
- What are you doing?

8
00:00:22.222 --> 00:00:23.281
I'm saving my brother.

9
00:00:23.457 --> 00:00:25.097
Don't tell your brother
what we're doing.

10
00:00:28.328 --> 00:00:29.591
<i>She's cracked the code.</i>

11
00:00:54.454 --> 00:00:55.922
God locked The Darkness away.

12
00:00:56.189 --> 00:01:00.183
<i>And He created a mark that
would serve as lock and key.</i>

13
00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:04.661
<i>The Mark cannot be removed.
lest The Darkness be set free.</i>

14
00:01:46.506 --> 00:01:47.565
Hey!

15
00:01:50.177 --> 00:01:51.645
The hell's going on?

16
00:02:39.926 --> 00:02:40.985
Hold on!

17
00:02:46.366 --> 00:02:47.459
Dean?

18
00:02:48.435 --> 00:02:49.435
Dean!

19
00:03:00.914 --> 00:03:02.041
Dean?

20
00:03:36.249 --> 00:03:37.273
Hey!

21
00:03:37.784 --> 00:03:39.013
<i>Hey!</i>

22
00:03:43.990 --> 00:03:45.253
You okay?

23
00:03:48.462 --> 00:03:49.623
Yeah.

24
00:03:50.831 --> 00:03:52.265
Where's the car?

25
00:03:54.267 --> 00:03:55.462
It's...

26
00:03:57.037 --> 00:03:59.199
- About a mile that way.
- What?

27
00:04:00.040 --> 00:04:01.040
Seriously?

28
00:04:03.143 --> 00:04:05.578
The Darkness hit.
You disappeared.

29
00:04:06.346 --> 00:04:07.746
You remember none of this?

30
00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:14.649
Hold on!

31
00:04:29.136 --> 00:04:30.468
She saved me.

32
00:04:31.404 --> 00:04:33.430
What? Who?

33
00:04:39.379 --> 00:04:40.472
The Darkness.

34
00:05:01.201 --> 00:05:03.932
Wait a second. what do
you mean she saved you?

35
00:05:04.104 --> 00:05:06.182
You were there. When the
storm hit. everything went dark.

36
00:05:06.206 --> 00:05:08.072
Yeah. but you just
disappeared from the car.

37
00:05:08.241 --> 00:05:09.470
I don't even remember that.

38
00:05:09.643 --> 00:05:11.771
Well. I don't remember
some woman pulling you out.

39
00:05:11.945 --> 00:05:13.122
Well. what do you
want me to say. okay?

40
00:05:13.146 --> 00:05:14.423
I was in the car. and
then I wasn't in the car.

41
00:05:14.447 --> 00:05:16.211
I was in the field.
and she was there.

42
00:05:16.550 --> 00:05:18.070
And she told you she
was The Darkness?

43
00:05:18.218 --> 00:05:20.278
No. She was wearing a
nametag. What do you think?

44
00:05:23.690 --> 00:05:24.919
She thanked me.

45
00:05:25.992 --> 00:05:26.992
For what?

46
00:05:27.460 --> 00:05:28.985
Setting her free.

47
00:05:31.331 --> 00:05:33.061
You didn't set her
free. I set her free.

48
00:05:33.233 --> 00:05:35.725
Does it matter? I mean.
yeah. you said the spell.

49
00:05:35.902 --> 00:05:37.928
but I had the Mark.
so lock and key.

50
00:05:38.104 --> 00:05:40.016
So. what? Now. she feels
indebted to you or something?

51
00:05:40.040 --> 00:05:42.339
I don't know. she's The
Darkness. Does she feel anything?

52
00:05:42.576 --> 00:05:44.374
And that's all she said? Thanks?

53
00:05:44.911 --> 00:05:46.140
Yeah. She was weird.

54
00:05:46.313 --> 00:05:49.442
But she had this energy
about her. This... This focus.

55
00:05:50.217 --> 00:05:51.708
But. yeah. not a talker.

56
00:05:52.285 --> 00:05:53.285
So. we know jack.

57
00:05:54.020 --> 00:05:56.065
Well. we know what she looks
like. We know that she's evil.

58
00:05:56.089 --> 00:05:57.751
Question is. what does she know?

59
00:05:57.924 --> 00:06:00.018
She's been locked away
since beginning of time.

60
00:06:00.193 --> 00:06:02.788
She even know what
a cheeseburger is?

61
00:06:03.029 --> 00:06:04.240
All I know is that
we set her free.

62
00:06:04.264 --> 00:06:06.665
and we're gonna put her
back in no matter what it takes.

63
00:06:08.635 --> 00:06:09.967
What the...

64
00:06:12.806 --> 00:06:15.105
- Just gonna let me get in the car?
- You were on a roll.

65
00:06:35.829 --> 00:06:36.853
Don't!

66
00:06:37.397 --> 00:06:38.421
Please!

67
00:06:39.065 --> 00:06:41.091
You think you can kill
me. you execrable...

68
00:07:30.784 --> 00:07:31.808
No.

69
00:07:37.123 --> 00:07:38.751
He's still alive.

70
00:07:55.075 --> 00:07:56.509
Don't make me hurt you.

71
00:07:57.243 --> 00:07:58.768
<i>Do you hear me?</i>

72
00:07:59.245 --> 00:08:01.908
I can't help myself.
You have to run.

73
00:09:01.474 --> 00:09:04.205
<i>Seen Ron? He hasn't
checked in in a while.</i>

74
00:09:04.377 --> 00:09:05.572
<i>You know where he is?</i>

75
00:09:31.671 --> 00:09:33.572
The hell happened here?

76
00:09:37.811 --> 00:09:38.972
Hello?

77
00:09:42.148 --> 00:09:43.446
Oh. that's not a happy sight.

78
00:09:43.783 --> 00:09:44.910
Hey. easy. buddy.

79
00:09:45.085 --> 00:09:48.681
Just stay cool till we figure
out what's going on here. okay?

80
00:09:50.457 --> 00:09:51.817
Kind of narrowing
my options here.

81
00:09:53.126 --> 00:09:54.326
We don't even know what he is.

82
00:09:58.331 --> 00:10:00.129
Weapons on the ground. Slow.

83
00:10:00.366 --> 00:10:02.886
Whoa. whoa. whoa. Easy. Officer.
We're FBI. okay? We got badges.

84
00:10:03.069 --> 00:10:04.503
Don't.

85
00:10:05.205 --> 00:10:06.867
- Show me some skin.
- Huh?

86
00:10:07.107 --> 00:10:08.632
- What?
- Both of you.

87
00:10:09.776 --> 00:10:11.039
This like a <i>Magic Mike</i> moment?

88
00:10:11.244 --> 00:10:12.268
Your throats.

89
00:10:13.680 --> 00:10:15.205
You... You think we're...

90
00:10:15.381 --> 00:10:16.859
Look. we don't even
know what these are.

91
00:10:16.883 --> 00:10:18.360
I need to know
you're not one of them.

92
00:10:18.384 --> 00:10:19.784
- One of what?
- Let's go!

93
00:10:19.953 --> 00:10:22.479
Okay. All right. Look. See?

94
00:10:22.956 --> 00:10:23.980
Good.

95
00:10:24.157 --> 00:10:26.490
- Let's see those IDs.
<i>- Yeah.</i>

96
00:10:27.160 --> 00:10:28.160
Whoa.

97
00:10:28.561 --> 00:10:31.087
All right. take...
Take it easy. okay?

98
00:10:31.931 --> 00:10:32.955
Bad guys?

99
00:10:34.033 --> 00:10:35.365
Rebar.

100
00:10:35.535 --> 00:10:36.594
I sought cover.

101
00:10:36.769 --> 00:10:38.465
I fell.

102
00:10:39.339 --> 00:10:41.501
Okay. why don't you tell
us what happened here?

103
00:10:42.642 --> 00:10:44.941
911 reported family in distress.

104
00:10:45.111 --> 00:10:47.351
I arrived to find several
hostiles attacking said family.

105
00:10:48.781 --> 00:10:50.215
Oh. God. It was horrible.

106
00:10:50.383 --> 00:10:52.063
How long have you
been on the job. Deputy?

107
00:10:52.886 --> 00:10:55.549
Uh... Okay. three weeks.

108
00:10:56.589 --> 00:10:57.750
Okay.

109
00:10:57.924 --> 00:10:59.984
Uh. I'm Dean. this is Sam.

110
00:11:00.660 --> 00:11:02.128
Just breathe. okay?

111
00:11:02.295 --> 00:11:04.059
Speak plain. What happened?

112
00:11:04.797 --> 00:11:05.797
They killed them all.

113
00:11:06.299 --> 00:11:08.165
- Who?
- Road crew.

114
00:11:08.334 --> 00:11:09.632
It was...

115
00:11:09.802 --> 00:11:10.895
They were like rabid dogs.

116
00:11:11.070 --> 00:11:13.665
I fired off a warning.
but they didn't stop.

117
00:11:13.840 --> 00:11:14.899
They were...

118
00:11:15.074 --> 00:11:16.440
You killed all these?

119
00:11:16.809 --> 00:11:18.769
I knew some of those
boys. but they didn't look...

120
00:11:19.245 --> 00:11:21.544
<i>Something was
wrong. they were...</i>

121
00:11:21.881 --> 00:11:22.881
They're not human.

122
00:11:28.254 --> 00:11:30.246
Okay. look. I
can stitch that up.

123
00:11:30.423 --> 00:11:32.583
But it's gonna be ugly. You
got a hospital around here?

124
00:11:32.692 --> 00:11:33.716
Yeah. up the road.

125
00:11:34.794 --> 00:11:37.286
All right. Here we go.

126
00:11:44.938 --> 00:11:46.964
Well. this is encouraging.

127
00:11:49.108 --> 00:11:50.599
Just wait here.

128
00:11:56.749 --> 00:11:58.775
So. what are you thinking?

129
00:11:59.953 --> 00:12:02.081
I really don't
know what to think.

130
00:12:02.488 --> 00:12:06.482
And I don't know what to expect.
either. so I'm just gonna chuck it all in.

131
00:12:06.993 --> 00:12:08.757
This is The Darkness.
right? It's got to be.

132
00:12:09.596 --> 00:12:11.740
So. what. she shows up and
everybody goes <i>28 Days Later?</i>

133
00:12:11.764 --> 00:12:12.764
I mean. we didn't.

134
00:12:13.600 --> 00:12:15.569
Yeah. but I was in the
car. And... And you...

135
00:12:15.735 --> 00:12:16.815
You said she protected you.

136
00:12:16.970 --> 00:12:20.338
So. I mean. maybe it wasn't her.
maybe it was the smoke. you know?

137
00:12:20.506 --> 00:12:24.466
Anybody who was outside. like the...
The road crew. they were exposed.

138
00:12:24.644 --> 00:12:26.408
I mean. you saw that.
That wasn't human.

139
00:12:26.713 --> 00:12:28.272
So. what. the smoke
mutated them?

140
00:12:29.282 --> 00:12:31.660
Yeah. sure. Why not? Just a
couple of hours ago I killed Death.

141
00:12:31.684 --> 00:12:33.152
I'm pretty much
open for anything.

142
00:12:33.319 --> 00:12:34.582
But mutated into what?

143
00:12:35.788 --> 00:12:37.099
All right. you know
what? One thing at a time.

144
00:12:37.123 --> 00:12:38.283
Let's just get her some help.

145
00:12:38.324 --> 00:12:40.084
And then we'll deal with
whatever comes next.

146
00:12:48.034 --> 00:12:49.263
I got to call this in.

147
00:12:49.435 --> 00:12:50.926
No. bad idea.

148
00:12:51.104 --> 00:12:52.197
More people. more bodies.

149
00:12:52.372 --> 00:12:53.635
We'll deal with this.

150
00:12:54.507 --> 00:12:56.352
You know what. Dean. I'm
gonna take a look around.

151
00:12:56.376 --> 00:12:57.400
You sew her up.

152
00:12:57.577 --> 00:12:59.705
All right. Do you
know this place?

153
00:12:59.979 --> 00:13:00.979
- This way.
- Okay.

154
00:14:13.453 --> 00:14:15.979
This is gonna hurt
like a son of a bitch.

155
00:14:20.960 --> 00:14:22.826
I knew those boys' sisters.

156
00:14:22.995 --> 00:14:23.995
Their parents.

157
00:14:24.664 --> 00:14:26.997
Yeah. well. you did what
you were trained to do.

158
00:14:27.200 --> 00:14:29.328
Sorry.

159
00:14:30.503 --> 00:14:32.183
They don't train you
to shoot your friends.

160
00:14:32.338 --> 00:14:34.034
I panicked. I could've...

161
00:14:34.907 --> 00:14:36.466
Those boys weren't boys.

162
00:14:36.642 --> 00:14:39.237
They were monsters
and they were a threat.

163
00:14:39.445 --> 00:14:41.607
Anybody could've panicked.

164
00:14:42.315 --> 00:14:44.307
But not anybody could've
done what you did.

165
00:14:46.652 --> 00:14:49.486
This job was supposed
to be saving people.

166
00:14:50.723 --> 00:14:52.089
Yeah. well.

167
00:14:53.059 --> 00:14:55.688
it sounds better
on paper. doesn't it?

168
00:14:59.799 --> 00:15:03.395
Well. now that you said your thanks.
let's talk about what happens next.

169
00:15:04.537 --> 00:15:06.062
I like it here.

170
00:15:06.973 --> 00:15:08.236
With you.

171
00:15:09.108 --> 00:15:13.204
I haven't felt this peaceful
in a long. long time.

172
00:15:13.813 --> 00:15:16.493
Well. let's get something straight.
I'm not here to bring you peace.

173
00:15:16.582 --> 00:15:18.016
I know what you are.

174
00:15:19.185 --> 00:15:20.380
Really?

175
00:15:21.254 --> 00:15:23.553
I've been gone so long I didn't
think anyone remembered.

176
00:15:23.756 --> 00:15:25.748
Well. Death painted
a hell of a picture.

177
00:15:26.793 --> 00:15:28.694
I don't know this Death.

178
00:15:28.928 --> 00:15:31.762
And he doesn't know me.

179
00:15:34.267 --> 00:15:36.634
Well. you're saying I shouldn't
try to kill you right now?

180
00:15:36.803 --> 00:15:38.431
Am I saying that?

181
00:15:40.440 --> 00:15:41.669
Or are you?

182
00:16:24.150 --> 00:16:25.174
Hello?

183
00:16:27.487 --> 00:16:28.853
<i>Is he dead?</i>

184
00:16:31.123 --> 00:16:32.682
Yeah. Um...

185
00:16:33.426 --> 00:16:34.917
Yeah. he's dead.

186
00:16:35.328 --> 00:16:38.924
It's okay to come
out. I'm. uh. FBI.

187
00:16:40.466 --> 00:16:41.559
Here.

188
00:16:42.568 --> 00:16:44.560
I'm gonna slide my badge
under the door. okay?

189
00:16:57.683 --> 00:17:00.346
Help us. Please.

190
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:47.732
Bollocks.

191
00:17:55.241 --> 00:17:56.869
Old-school it is.

192
00:18:05.651 --> 00:18:08.450
Vanilla spice?

193
00:18:08.621 --> 00:18:10.487
<i>Marn? Down here!</i>

194
00:18:12.792 --> 00:18:13.792
Hmm.

195
00:18:20.900 --> 00:18:21.900
What's going on?

196
00:18:22.268 --> 00:18:23.628
You just sit your
tush down. okay?

197
00:18:23.803 --> 00:18:25.135
Just let me get this out.

198
00:18:26.839 --> 00:18:28.383
I've been thinking a
lot about what you said.

199
00:18:28.407 --> 00:18:30.688
And. I know. I lost my chickens
when you put it out there.

200
00:18:30.776 --> 00:18:33.746
but it's not every day that your wife
tells you that she wants to watch you

201
00:18:33.913 --> 00:18:35.424
get a party started
with your best friends.

202
00:18:35.448 --> 00:18:37.747
I mean. am I right?

203
00:18:39.385 --> 00:18:40.385
Hmm.

204
00:18:40.953 --> 00:18:42.148
Go on.

205
00:18:42.321 --> 00:18:46.417
So. I slept on it. and I prayed
on it. and then it came to me.

206
00:18:47.159 --> 00:18:48.457
YOLO.

207
00:18:49.061 --> 00:18:50.256
YOLO?

208
00:18:50.429 --> 00:18:52.455
"You Only Live Once."

209
00:18:55.067 --> 00:18:56.558
- Don't.
- Sorry.

210
00:18:56.736 --> 00:18:58.136
So. I called Dale.
and he said...

211
00:18:58.304 --> 00:18:59.795
H-E-double hockey sticks. yeah!

212
00:18:59.972 --> 00:19:01.201
<i>Dale ran it by Deb.</i>

213
00:19:01.374 --> 00:19:03.900
We were only gonna
get buffet. anyway.

214
00:19:04.243 --> 00:19:05.575
And here we are.

215
00:19:05.978 --> 00:19:07.589
I didn't think I'd be
this nervous. but...

216
00:19:07.613 --> 00:19:08.876
Oh. hey. hey. don't worry.

217
00:19:09.048 --> 00:19:11.813
- We'll be gentle. Not!
- Oh. Dale!

218
00:19:12.051 --> 00:19:13.542
Hmm.

219
00:19:14.220 --> 00:19:16.746
Any-hoot. it's your
day. birthday girl.

220
00:19:16.922 --> 00:19:21.257
You just say go. and heck.
we will light this candle.

221
00:19:22.528 --> 00:19:23.528
<i>Marn?</i>

222
00:19:23.796 --> 00:19:25.287
Everything okay with the car?

223
00:19:27.099 --> 00:19:29.432
Oh...

224
00:19:30.336 --> 00:19:31.702
It's fine.

225
00:19:31.871 --> 00:19:33.271
Just fine.

226
00:19:35.408 --> 00:19:38.936
The doc said it was gonna
be a tough birth. but Janie.

227
00:19:40.813 --> 00:19:41.872
she stepped up.

228
00:19:43.149 --> 00:19:45.550
<i>That twister hit.
the power went out.</i>

229
00:19:46.152 --> 00:19:48.178
She just kept on going.

230
00:19:49.288 --> 00:19:50.312
No drugs.

231
00:19:53.225 --> 00:19:56.286
Just pushed out this little
dewdrop like she was nothing.

232
00:20:00.900 --> 00:20:03.028
Then Janie started bleeding.

233
00:20:05.271 --> 00:20:06.933
They tried. but...

234
00:20:09.275 --> 00:20:11.475
You'd think they'd know how
to stop something like that.

235
00:20:13.279 --> 00:20:14.679
I'm so sorry. Mike.

236
00:20:16.148 --> 00:20:18.174
You think you could tell
us what happened here?

237
00:20:19.151 --> 00:20:20.949
I went outside after.

238
00:20:22.521 --> 00:20:24.183
To collect myself.

239
00:20:25.858 --> 00:20:27.486
A truckload of them pulled up.

240
00:20:28.427 --> 00:20:29.588
The road crew?

241
00:20:31.163 --> 00:20:33.132
They didn't say nothing.

242
00:20:33.833 --> 00:20:35.301
They just went off.

243
00:20:36.168 --> 00:20:38.967
<i>Attacking folks like
they were possessed.</i>

244
00:20:39.739 --> 00:20:42.573
I tore back inside
to get this little one.

245
00:20:43.476 --> 00:20:46.036
Found that supply closet and.

246
00:20:46.212 --> 00:20:48.443
you know. I've been there since.

247
00:20:49.515 --> 00:20:50.676
<i>I could hear them. though.</i>

248
00:20:50.950 --> 00:20:52.976
Tearing through the halls.

249
00:20:53.586 --> 00:20:54.610
Doctors. nurses.

250
00:20:55.554 --> 00:20:56.886
They didn't care.

251
00:21:07.199 --> 00:21:09.395
<i>You said the road
crew went nuts.</i>

252
00:21:09.735 --> 00:21:10.862
<i>Any of them come after you?</i>

253
00:21:11.036 --> 00:21:12.299
Yeah. a few of them.

254
00:21:12.838 --> 00:21:16.297
Did they cut you
or bleed on you?

255
00:21:20.246 --> 00:21:21.246
They did.

256
00:21:23.949 --> 00:21:25.469
<i>I don't understand. What are...</i>

257
00:21:25.918 --> 00:21:27.147
What are you saying?

258
00:21:27.319 --> 00:21:32.019
He's saying that whatever
this is. it might be transmittable.

259
00:21:32.191 --> 00:21:34.660
What? We don't even
